                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-05-05</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Fred's book offers an excellent first-hand account into the world of a baseball GM.  His stories and experiences help to shed some light on what it takes to become a successful sport executive.  I don't think there is any better way to learn how to become successful in this business than through someonee who did it himself.  This book is excellent for sport management classes as it shows students what skills are necessary in different situations.  A MUST READ, I will put this book in my baseball library as one of the most useful books on the business of baseball.  </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A Great Trip As a Dodger Fan</div>
                    <div>
